text: The Swartz Covered Bridge, near Wyandot, Ohio, was built in 1880. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1976. It is a Howe truss covered bridge. It is located northwest of Wyandot on County Road 130, in Antrim Township, Wyandot County, Ohio. It is covered in the Ohio Historic Places Dictionary. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Covered bridges in Ohio Category:National Register of Historic Places in Wyandot County, Ohio Category:Bridges completed in 1880
